.SH NAME
drm_self_refresh_helper_update_avg_times \- Updates a crtc's SR time averages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_self_refresh_helper_update_avg_times
.BI "(struct drm_atomic_state *state "  ","
.BI "unsigned int commit_time_ms "  ","
.BI "unsigned int new_self_refresh_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
the state which has just been applied to hardware
.IP "commit_time_ms" 12
the amount of time in ms that this commit took to complete
.IP "new_self_refresh_mask" 12
bitmask of crtc's that have self_refresh_active in
new state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called after \fIdrm_mode_config_funcs.atomic_commit_tail\fP, this function will
update the average entry/exit self refresh times on self refresh transitions.
These averages will be used when calculating how long to delay before
entering self refresh mode after activity.
